      "query": "We need to order an unreinforced, easy-flowing PA66 resin for injection molding electrical connectors. Which specific BASF Ultramid A grade is the standard recommendation for this application?",
      "agent": {
        "text": "For unreinforced, easy-flowing PA66 resin used to injection-mold electrical connectors, the standard BASF recommendation is **Ultramid\u00ae A3K**. \n\nIf the connectors will be subjected to elevated long-term temperatures, the heat-stabilized counterpart is **Ultramid\u00ae A3W**. \n\n*   **Ultramid\u00ae A3K**: This is the baseline unreinforced, easy-flowing PA66 grade. BASF\u2019s technical datasheets explicitly recommend it for fast-processing, highly stressed technical components and electrically insulating parts like terminals and cable connectors.\n*   **Ultramid\u00ae A3W**: This grade provides the identical unreinforced, easy-flowing injection-molding characteristics as A3K but includes a heat-aging resistant additive package. It is strictly recommended for coil formers, bearing cages, and cable connectors exposed to thermal stress.\n\nBoth are real, actively orderable SKUs in the Ultramid A (PA66) catalog. When ordering, you will need to specify the base grade alongside your desired color code (e.g., Natural, or BK464 for black).",
