      "query": "We are switching our SBS hot-melt adhesive formulation and need a multifunctional phenolic antioxidant. What exact BASF Irganox part number should we issue the purchase order for to replace our current stabilizer?",
      "agent": {
        "text": "You should issue your purchase order for **BASF Irganox\u00ae 1726** (CAS: 110675-26-8).\n\nAccording to BASF's technical catalog data, Irganox 1726 is a multifunctional phenolic antioxidant explicitly optimized for stabilizing organic polymers, particularly hot-melt adhesives based on unsaturated block copolymers like SBS (styrene-butadiene-styrene) and SIS. It acts as a highly effective thermo-oxidative stabilizer, providing excellent viscosity retention and color stability during processing and high-temperature aging. It can be used alone at low concentrations (typically 0.1% \u2013 1.0%) without needing co-stabilizers.\n\n**Important Purchasing Notes:**\n*   **Irganox\u00ae 565:** This is another valid multifunctional phenolic antioxidant compatible with SBS. However, Irganox 1726 is typically the preferred industry standard for superior viscosity and color control in styrenic hot melts. \n*   **Irganox\u00ae 1520 L:** Do not order this SKU. Although it is also a multifunctional liquid phenolic antioxidant, BASF explicitly warns in their datasheets that 1520 L is *not recommended* for odor-sensitive hot-melt adhesives.\n\nSpecify **BASF Irganox 1726** on your PO to ensure the correct, formulation-compatible additive for your new SBS hot-melt line.",
